1.^^^^^^^^^^My analysis of Tic tac toe seems similar in kind to that of Michael Clarke's two chess endgames described in Berliner's review of the literature (1978) and characterized as developing "a database of perfect information".   A different view of Tic tac toe is presented by Newell and Simon (1972, p.62).  They offer the productions below as embodying what "is generally regarded as a good strategy for the first player".2
.ds
